review_blob:
Before Itasted it, my guess would be.. "Awesome, it tastes like gatorade (10 seconds later) ugh, it sucks."
After tasting it: I was right on.
Smooth lager, great palate, which I rarely notice.  Easy to drink and youll enjoy it as long as youre not overly picky.
If there was ever a creamsicle flavored beer, this would be it.  Pretty fruity, not very beery, but still not a bad drink.
beer_name: Buffalo Bills Orange Blossom Cream Ale

review_blob: Samuel Smiths always makes top of the line brews in my opinion, and of course this one is no exception. The aftertaste finishes fast and has ample hoppiness.
Very bitter beer, went well with a cheesesteak.  I would recommend seeking this beer out if youve never tried it
Easy to drink and pretty smooth.  Have to be careful pouring it though because the head will overflow the glass very quickly. Not a bad beer if you want to drink a few.
Pretty gross. Ice beers are just bad news. Stay away from this one people. Color and aroma are exactly what youd expect, taste is a little worse than it should be.
Vladivostok. Slightly better than the Russian beers I was drinking, obviously brewed to be easy to drink and not offer much flavor.
Light yellow color, very foamy. Below average session beer. Nothing special about it

Considering the fact Im drinking a can of this beer in China and it probably took way too long to get here its pretty good. Has citrusy notes. Long lasting finish, but some of that might be due to the beers long journey
Well, Ive had better beer from worse breweries I guess. NondeScript really, just drinkable when no other options are available, like airport restaurants
Had this on a flight from San Fran to Beijing.  Under any other circumstance, one should avoid it.  Everything youd expect from a pale lager. Yay
A very hoppy beer is sure way to make it a hit. To me the thing that sets this beer apart is its very smooth finish and long-lasting but not-too-crazy finish.

Without a doubt the Hoppiest beer Ive ever had.  I knew right after that moment that it would be ranked really highly on this site.  It was a little too much for me, but it definitely wasnt bad, Id like to try it again one day.
Dark brown, head vanished before I carried it back to my table. Great malty flavor, not too hoppy. Very enjoyable beer
I dont think the presidente of this company ever bothered to imbibe this beer, because, somehow it is a tier below the other bad pale lagers
Pale lager, nothing great.  Its only virtue is the ease of which this beer can be drunk.

Unbelievably carbonated. Drank it from a paper cup, which is what this beer deserves. One of very few people who have had the misfortune of drinking this beer. It might be impossible to stomach enough of this stuff get a buzz
Not as good the Dinkel Acker Dark, in fact, I wouldnt consider this a session beer. I would be hard pressed to say one thing that sets this beer apart from the crowd
Light color, but dont let that fool you, its better than most beers of the same shade. It is very enjoyable
beer_name: Samuel Smiths Pure Brewed Organic Lager

review_blob: If you ever had a hankerin to try a Ukrainian beer, this might be your best chance, otherwise, you might as well stick to Bud
Very bitter, but I dont think it was due to the hops.  The skunky, bitter aftertaste lasts longer than one would like
Hmm, nondeScript. Slight hints of hops, didnt taste much, if any citrus. A little too carbonated
Much better than most hefeweizens out there.  While it has the usual citrus overtones, but has more hops than average.
Well, its a pale lager, so expectations have to be low. Nothing stands out about this beer other than have a slightly cooler can than other beers in the genre.
On tap in Chicago. Has a great citrus flavor, not much head or carbonation so its pretty smooth too. One could definitely drink a bunch of these in one sitting.
beer_name: Three Floyds Pride & Joy Mild Ale

review_blob: Despite the great commercials, I failed to see the light after I drank this beer. Just another pale lager.
Complex flavor indeed, it would be difficult to describe all the flavors that are involved. Just keeping it simple and reporting it as being quite enjoyable.

I guess the big brewers just make ginormous quantities of pale lagers and pour it into bottles with different labels. In a blind taste test, this beer would taste exactly the same as about 50 beers Ive tried.

Giant can! Vikings are cool. Thats where this beers appeal ends.  It is just an uninspired beer that tastes just like everything else that is mass produced, I think I tasted a little bit of citrus, but Im not sure.
Had some on top, I thought the tap was hilarious (beer can).  This beer really surprised me, dry and not too bitter from start to finish, goes down very smoothly. Not as hoppy as a lot of other IPAs.
One of the more carbonated beers Ive ever drank.  It is right on par with other strong ales.  Not very smooth, but the flavor does have a hint of fruit and alcohol, which is okay every now and then.
This beer kind of taste OK at first, but the stale grass aftertaste is enough to scare me off for life. There are many better options at every bar.
Being the first sour ale I ever drank, it is impossible to compare this one against its peers.  However, it was a very refreshing beer, nice tart taste. I wouldnt mind drinking it again.
While this beer is a very good one, it has a strong flavor which is done just right, Id say this is their hoppiest beer.  If you drink a Chimay you cant go wrong.

This beer has a very complex, interesting flavor.  Right away it becomes apparent that the people at Chimay know exactly what theyre doing. The beer has a long lasting finish that is actually enjoyable.
Samuel Smith never misses.  I usually do not like stouts, but this beer ended up my all time favorite beer.  All I can say is try it!
Theyre definitely not lying when they say this is a blueberry beer.  Since Im not a fan of blueberries I cannot rate it very high.  Nothing great about this one, but nothing awful either.
Very hoppy beer, deep amber color, short-lived aftertaste. Very similar to normal Sam Adams

You cannot disrespect the high life.  For the money, this beer is great.  Has a much better flavor than all the other cheap 30 pack beers. And when it comes in the 40 oz bottle it is the best 40 also.

Not completely what I expected from a Samuel Smith brew. As with anything Organic, its not as good, its probably not really organic, but it might be bought up buy the elusive hippie demographic.  Then again it is a pale lager, so its better than its competitors in this market, and its understandable why SS would make this
On tap at Lulus.  Head fizzles off very quickly, but thats expected. Has just the right level of hoppiness in my opinion, could have a little better finish. Still I would highly recommend it.
Bottle. It was delicious, subtle citrus undertones. I drank it in Hawaii, so it must not skunk fast
To me, this beer was a lot better than many of the other pale lagers of the world. Still, its nothing to brag about. A little better than what I expected from a PL.
This was a very good beer. Has a great, complex flavor that goes down smoothly.
Found this on tap in Waikiki. Interesting, it was smooth yet highly carbonated. So be prepared to burp a lot.
Gross.  Kind of tastes like how Id imagine skunk cabbage beer would taste if that existed.  I would consider it the Pabst of the Pacific.
Dab is a gentle beer that doesnt stand out in any way. Its a step above all the light colored pilseners that clog up the shelves
This beer gets max appearance because they have cool beer taps.  If youre in Chicagoland then you must have this beer
I dont how their uber brewing methods hasnt made this the worlds most superior beer, but it a fine beer indeed
